1
00:00:05,530 --> 00:00:09,672
We are all familiar 
with the expression 
 

2
00:00:09,672 --> 00:00:13,682
‘No risk, no gain.’

3
00:00:13,682 --> 00:00:16,092
If you’re going to gain something, 
you have to take some risk.

4
00:00:16,122 --> 00:00:20,840
[All Gain, No Risk]

5
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:27,930
At the time I was very sort of pleased
with myself about that.

6
00:00:27,930 --> 00:00:33,567
And I thought, “Yeah, 
I’ve risked everything to be with you,

7
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:37,997
to come in connection with your holy lotus feet,
and now I’ve gained everything.”

8
00:00:38,025 --> 00:00:41,878
So, I was very proud 
and happy, like,

9
00:00:41,878 --> 00:00:45,340
“Yes, I know that very well—
‘no risk, no gain’,

10
00:00:45,340 --> 00:00:51,270
and I myself am
such a sterling example of that.”

11
00:00:51,270 --> 00:00:53,725
And then Guru Mahārāj knew, 
he had me

12
00:00:53,725 --> 00:00:56,545
like primed for what 
he was about to say,

13
00:00:56,545 --> 00:00:58,486
because I was sitting like that 
[self-mocking]

14
00:00:58,486 --> 00:01:01,538
And he said, 
“But there is a higher stage,”

15
00:01:01,538 --> 00:01:03,518
“There is? What?”

16
00:01:03,518 --> 00:01:08,490
He said, 
“All risk and no gain.”

17
00:01:08,490 --> 00:01:11,420
And I had to think 
for minute like,

18
00:01:11,420 --> 00:01:16,580
“Did I just hear what he said?
‘All risk and no gain.’”

19
00:01:16,580 --> 00:01:18,863
And he could see 
a bewildered look on my face.

20
00:01:18,863 --> 00:01:22,033
He said, 
“Are you ready for that?

21
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:26,363
You’ll risk everything 
and gain nothing.”

22
00:01:26,363 --> 00:01:31,874
And then I thought … 
I was trying to think of it all, but …

23
00:01:31,874 --> 00:01:35,674
and I am unable 
to process this entirely.

24
00:01:35,674 --> 00:01:40,535
And then now I’m totally bewildered, 
and Guru Mahārāj is smiling.

25
00:01:40,535 --> 00:01:41,905
[Laughing]

26
00:01:42,285 --> 00:01:45,631
And he said,
“That is the position of the Vraja-gopīs.

27
00:01:45,631 --> 00:01:50,581
They risk everything 
with no anticipation of gaining.

28
00:01:50,581 --> 00:01:55,481
That’s the highest standard. 
They’re not calculating self-interest,

29
00:01:55,481 --> 00:02:00,071
they’re not calculating 
what they will get from doing this.

30
00:02:00,095 --> 00:02:03,802
bhajanīya-sarva-sad-guṇa viśiṣṭa
[Bs]

31
00:02:03,802 --> 00:02:09,644
They’re irresistibly drawn to Kṛṣṇa
to offer themselves.”

32
00:02:09,644 --> 00:02:13,539
Just like in the parallel, 
a mundane parallel in this world,

33
00:02:13,539 --> 00:02:16,919
when someone in romantic love

34
00:02:16,919 --> 00:02:20,338
and they become enamoured 
by another person 
 

35
00:02:20,338 --> 00:02:24,058
without thinking 
about all these things—

36
00:02:24,058 --> 00:02:29,028
automatically they’re giving themselves
to that person.

37
00:02:29,043 --> 00:02:34,219
Even more so when one
in the consume someone or something,

38
00:02:34,219 --> 00:02:38,369
we’re actually searching for someone 
to offer ourselves to,

39
00:02:38,369 --> 00:02:41,279
to give ourselves to.

40
00:02:41,279 --> 00:02:46,846
But because we’ve been deceived
so many times,

41
00:02:46,846 --> 00:02:53,829
and we have a strong tendency 
ourselves toward self‒deception,

42
00:02:53,829 --> 00:02:56,049
 
we’re reluctant.

43
00:02:56,049 --> 00:03:01,505
So we are keeping the heart 
sheltered, cloistered, covered,

44
00:03:01,505 --> 00:03:06,225
and afraid to give ourselves, 
to offer ourselves.

45
00:03:06,225 --> 00:03:12,727
So, anyway, Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said, 
“All risk and no gain.

46
00:03:12,727 --> 00:03:15,517
Are you ready for that?”

47
00:03:15,517 --> 00:03:20,114
And now I was just 
totally bewildered.

48
00:03:20,114 --> 00:03:24,194
I don’t know 
what I’m agreeing to.

49
00:03:24,194 --> 00:03:28,024
And then he began to explain.
He said,

50
00:03:28,324 --> 00:03:31,204
“All risk and no gain because

51
00:03:31,204 --> 00:03:35,584
you think that 
this world is something substantial.

52
00:03:35,584 --> 00:03:42,762
And you think that spiritual life 
and spiritual reality is insubstantial.”

53
00:03:42,762 --> 00:03:45,511
It’s just something abstract 
people are talking about it.

54
00:03:45,511 --> 00:03:47,931
Can you prove it? 
This, that sort of thing.

55
00:03:47,931 --> 00:03:53,301
We are very suspicious
of the spiritual reality.

56
00:03:53,336 --> 00:03:55,367
But this world … because

57
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:58,677
you can knock on it,
you can walk on it,

58
00:03:58,677 --> 00:04:03,513
you can manipulate it 
in various ways,

59
00:04:03,513 --> 00:04:07,313
we think, “This is the solid 
substantial plane.”

60
00:04:07,313 --> 00:04:10,183
Although even according to the science
it’s constantly in motion,

61
00:04:10,183 --> 00:04:15,423
and also according to the science 
there will come a time when all of this vanishes.

62
00:04:15,423 --> 00:04:20,818
And enter some kind 
of nebulous state.

63
00:04:20,818 --> 00:04:23,308
And according to Veda 
it’ll again express itself.

64
00:04:23,308 --> 00:04:26,139
bhūtvā bhūtvā pralīyate 
[Bg: 8.19]

65
00:04:26,139 --> 00:04:28,299
It manifests for sometime,

66
00:04:28,299 --> 00:04:33,079
it’s all disintegrated and withdrawn, 
and then manifests again.

67
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:37,502
So, even though we know that 
that’s really the nature of this world,

68
00:04:37,502 --> 00:04:43,259
and everything we see here 
has only appeared for a brief time,

69
00:04:43,259 --> 00:04:45,593
and will vanish in time, 
we’re still thinking,

70
00:04:45,593 --> 00:04:49,513
“This is the solid world
with a strong foundation,

71
00:04:49,513 --> 00:04:54,456
and the spiritual world
that we’re hearing about in spiritual conception

72
00:04:54,456 --> 00:05:01,766
is very tentative, it’s abstract,
we are not sure,

73
00:05:01,766 --> 00:05:06,796
we’ll have to examine it more,
look at the fine print, etc.”

74
00:05:06,796 --> 00:05:09,181
So he said, 
“That’s why it’s ‘all risk and no gain’—

75
00:05:09,181 --> 00:05:13,191
all of this that 
I’ve accumulated here,

76
00:05:13,191 --> 00:05:15,611
in the world of exploitation,

77
00:05:15,611 --> 00:05:17,871
the energy that I’ve accumulated,
 

78
00:05:17,871 --> 00:05:25,151
I’m going to risk all of this 
in service to Kṛṣṇa,

79
00:05:25,151 --> 00:05:29,050
which seems 
to be something abstract,

80
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:34,280
and not palpable, inaccessible, etc.

81
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:38,664
But just as when you go East,

82
00:05:38,664 --> 00:05:41,684
automatically 
you’re withdrawing from West.

83
00:05:41,684 --> 00:05:49,067
As you engage in a process 
of self-surrender,

84
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:52,387
gradually you’ll begin to perceive:

85
00:05:52,387 --> 00:05:56,937
this world and everything in it 
is insubstantial,

86
00:05:56,937 --> 00:06:01,772
and actually what I’m coming in connection with 
in the Kṛṣṇa‒conscious world

87
00:06:01,772 --> 00:06:05,432
is real and substantial.”

88
00:06:05,432 --> 00:06:08,624
So, then the transition 
takes place.

89
00:06:08,624 --> 00:06:13,644
So, Guru Mahārāj  said,
“What initially seemed to be a proposition

90
00:06:13,644 --> 00:06:17,449
of ‘all risk and no gain’

91
00:06:17,449 --> 00:06:23,229
in the end becomes 
‘all gain and no risk.’”

92
00:06:23,229 --> 00:06:26,649
Because whatever was gathered here 
in the temporary world

93
00:06:26,649 --> 00:06:28,559
is not substantial to begin with.

94
00:06:28,559 --> 00:06:30,830
So, what did you really risk?

95
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:32,190
Nothing.

96
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:36,260
And you gained everything 
in the process.

97
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:38,759
So, in the end 
‘all risk and no gain’

98
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:42,249
turns into
‘all gain and no risk’.

99
00:06:44,261 --> 00:06:48,381
But how to proceed 
in that direction?

100
00:06:48,381 --> 00:06:53,657
If this concept 
awakens in the heart

101
00:06:53,657 --> 00:06:59,477
a little sense of potential, 
of possibility,

102
00:06:59,477 --> 00:07:02,996
then under the guidance 
of sādhu, sāstra, guru, Vaiṣṇava

103
00:07:02,996 --> 00:07:05,836
we try to make some progress.

